result.execSummary:
The defendant Natalie L Wolski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Natalie L Wolski in court with Attorney Carl William Chesshir.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Natalie Schiferl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #11.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #11.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Chesshir makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #11:  15 Days Jail  (17 days credit)  **TIME SERVED**

COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid out of cash bail posted ($200.00) and remainder due ($53.00) is paid in lieu of 2 days credit jail served (see above)
Wisconsin Community Service non-compliance letter received and filed.

Defendant Natalie L Wolski in court, in custody, with attorney Carl William Chesshir.   Lucas Paul Bennewitz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case called for Bail Motion hearing. Attorney Chesshir requests that the Defendant's signature bond be reinstated. State objects to any modification of bond. Court denies bail motion.   Bail remains as fixed. Atty Chesshir requests a hearing 30 days out to give update of negotiations. Court adjourns.  Hearing scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 09:00 am.
(Fax) Defendant's bail motion. Filed by Atty Chesshir.

Defendant to have no contact with co-defendant or Shavell B. or any Wal-Mart store.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Defendant to report/comply with Wisconsin Community Services Pretrial Supervision Program.  Defendant to report within the first business day after posting bail or released from custody.
